POSITION TITLE: Operations Intern 
POSITION SUMMARY: The Operations Intern will report to the Director of Operations and coordinate with the Chief Financial and Operating Officer.  The Operations Intern will support NECSN’s organization-wide operations efforts in the areas of internal systems, research, data management, member support, and event support.
RESPONSIBILITIES: The Operations Intern will work under the direction of the Director of Operations on the following:
Creating and implementing a system for capturing & recording information about building addresses for all New York Charter Schools;
Updating the organizations Member Relationship Management platform’s data system; 
Creating data analysis in Excel using the organization’s database of information about schools in New York and Connecticut (SQL experience helpful but not required); 
Assisting with overhauling the organization’s data management systems for Events and Annual Membership interactions;
Updating and maintaining NECSN’s membership email list;
Updating and maintaining NECSN’s school contacts list;
 Planning and coordinating logistics for events including:
The 20210 New York State Charter Schools Conference
Awareness/Advocacy Days
Charter school Leader convenings
Charter school Board Member convenings
Assisting with establishing a Vendor information repository for member schools; 
Identifying and merging various resources to create a compliance calendar for all charter schools in New York State;
Creating a library of free resources for educational and nonprofit institutions;
Creating a grant opportunity library for member schools;
Conducting research on other statewide charter schools associations; and
Other operations-related projects to be discussed with the Director of Operations.

The Northeast Charter Schools Network serves as the backbone for the New York Charter Schools Association and the Connecticut Charter Schools Association, the nonprofit membership organizations serving as the unified voice for the over 340 charter schools in the two states.  We fight to ensure that every child in New York and Connectciut has the opportunity to attend a great public charter school capable of unlocking his or her potential. Visit nycharters.net and ctcharters.org to learn more.
